Reasoning: The paper deals with polynomial identity testing algorithms for various models of arithmetic circuits, including read-once oblivious algebraic branching programs (ROABP) and depth-$3$ set-multilinear circuits. These topics are closely related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), scientific computing (cs.SC), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
